From wasm-cxx-shim Phase-7-B1 work-in-progress.
Wrap manifold's iostream-using OBJ I/O paths in `#ifndef MANIFOLD_NO_IOSTREAM`
so the library compiles when libc++'s localization machinery is disabled
(`_LIBCPP_HAS_LOCALIZATION=0` in the smoke test's `__config_site` override).

Three blocks:
- src/impl.cpp ~lines 152-159: `FromChars` template helper using
  std::istringstream
- src/impl.cpp ~lines 790-918: WriteOBJWithEpsilon, ReadOBJWithEpsilon,
  ReadOBJ (×2), WriteOBJ (×2), operator<<(ostream, Manifold::Impl)
- bindings/c/manifoldc.cpp ~lines 916-944: the C-API OBJ I/O bindings
  (manifold_read_obj, manifold_meshgl64_read_obj, manifold_write_obj,
  manifold_meshgl64_write_obj) — all use std::istringstream / stringstream

Originally documented in pca006132's manifold-on-wasm experiment:
  https://github.com/elalish/manifold/discussions/1046#discussioncomment-11302257

Generated against manifold v3.4.1.

Upstream PR target: elalish/manifold. Cleanest upstream form would
gate the OBJ I/O bits on a `MANIFOLD_NO_IOSTREAM` (or equivalently
named) build option. The patch here uses that macro name for forward
compatibility.

